manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Made in the USA All of our products are designed, printed, hand assembled, and packaged in the USA. Premium Quality We use only superior quality, responsibly sourced paper, card stock, and printing processes. Functional Design We love functional design, which means our products are both practical and beautiful. Female Solopreneur Our team includes freelancers and other small businesses, but the company is 100% owned by one woman.

Fine, Functional Stationery for Everyday Needs & Special Events 321Done offers a handcrafted collection of fine and functional stationery. Whether for everyday needs or special events, we believe that stationery should be as beautiful as it is practical - a belief that inspires every piece we create. From notepads to get you organized, to forms for your small business needs, to cards and invites to personalize your party, we have a little something for everyone. All of our stationery is proudly designed and printed in the USA, using only the finest quality materials. The paper is premium, the printing is sharp, the design is functional, and the result is a product we are proud to pass on to our fellow paper lovers. Browse the shop, see what's in store, and see why our customers are raving.

Blank Cards: Get Ready to Get Creative! Our white and kraft cards are a blank slate for your next design. Grab your fancy pens, pastels, markers, stickers, stamps - whatever you like - and get creative! These cards are great for making your own note cards, greeting cards, table cards, favor tags, thank yous... and so much more! ✔ Smooth, Matte, Superior Stock: Cards are made from smooth, matte, ultra heavy (14pt / 140lb / 300gsm) card stock. It's easy to work with, looks and feels great, and is a premium backdrop for your creative design. ✔ So Many Sizes: From mini 3.5 x 2 cards all the way up to 5 x 7, we have all the sizes you could ask for. ✔ Flat or Folding: Choose from flat or folding card options. Add a Pop of Color If completely blank is not your style, try our floral cards for your next project. They're offered in white and tan and in three designs. Ruled Cards: Get Ready to Get Organized! Dot Grid Cards Double-sided dot grid cards are pocket size, portable, and perfect for BUJO on the go. ✔ Thick & Sturdy: Made with 140lb smooth, matte card stock that stands up to your gel pens and markers. ✔ Several Sizes: Dot grid cards come in a range of sizes from small 3" x 5" to large 5" x 7." ✔ Double-Sided Dot Variety: Some people prefer small dots, some large. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I can’t say enough about this product! We bought several sizes to create a wedding invitation suite and they are PERFECT!!!! The preprinted florals were bold, true to color and crisp. The paper is 140lb CARD (i wouldn’t even say “cardstock” because it was so thick—not cheap feeling). We printed off hundreds of copies without a single issue. **We used the manual feed tray instead of the paper tray** Do not expect these thick cards to print from your printer’s paper tray!!! Any printing issues you have are due to the printer itself and not because of this product. We have a Brother Laser Printer and our ink did not smudge on the invitations. But I will admit that when we printed table numbers (in a very large and bold font) the ink did tend to smudge if it’s touched—again, this is a printer/ink issue and not due to the cardstock. The only drawback is not having more sizes to choose from. We ordered placecards, 4x6, and 5x7. Would love to see an 8.5x11 size to fold for programs or use for stationary. We saved HUNDREDS of dollars using this stationery!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This stationery is beautiful and very sturdy. However, my printer refused to print on 5x7 paper. So did the local Office Max. Office Depot, etc. Finally took the paper to a specialized print shop who printed my invitations without difficulty. They turned out wonderfully. No hesitation about the paper - just make sure you have the capability to print on it.
